WEBVTT

00:01.502 --> 00:02.461
<i>Previously on</i>
<i>"Promised Land"...</i>

00:04.338 --> 00:05.672
You're an American now.

00:05.672 --> 00:08.550
You should go by Joe.

00:08.550 --> 00:09.968
I took this little vineyard

00:09.968 --> 00:12.429
and turned it into one
of the largest wine producers

00:12.429 --> 00:13.347
in the country.

00:13.347 --> 00:14.848
Think about
what you built.

00:14.848 --> 00:17.100
Hey, what <i>we</i> built.

00:17.100 --> 00:18.560
I'm so proud of you, V.

00:18.560 --> 00:19.561
Thanks, Papi.

00:19.561 --> 00:21.146
To the new CEO.

00:21.146 --> 00:22.147
[ Body thumps ]

00:22.147 --> 00:23.190
[ Brakes squeal ]

00:24.274 --> 00:25.359
I'm Father Ramos.

00:25.359 --> 00:27.027
I told myself
you were dead.

00:27.027 --> 00:29.029
Woman: Billy.

00:29.029 --> 00:31.073
Your whole life
is based on a lie,

00:31.073 --> 00:32.241
Carlos Rincón.

00:32.241 --> 00:34.076
I am going
to buy your company

00:34.076 --> 00:35.244
right out from under you.

00:35.244 --> 00:37.496
I'm only the mother
to three of your kids.

00:37.496 --> 00:39.706
We can't let your mother
take our company.

00:39.706 --> 00:41.792
Oh, Antonio.
They are going to regret

00:41.792 --> 00:43.961
the day they turned their back
on you.

00:43.961 --> 00:46.088
It's good to be home.

00:46.088 --> 00:47.297
♪♪

00:47.297 --> 00:50.300
[ Singing in Spanish ]

00:50.300 --> 00:52.135
♪♪

00:52.135 --> 00:53.637
[ Breathing heavily ]

00:53.637 --> 01:02.062
♪♪

01:02.062 --> 01:10.571
♪♪

01:10.571 --> 01:11.780
Get up here.

01:11.780 --> 01:14.783
[ Singing in Spanish ]

01:14.783 --> 01:18.579
♪♪

01:18.579 --> 01:19.705
[ Breathing heavily ]

01:19.705 --> 01:22.207
[ Chuckles ]

01:22.207 --> 01:23.584
What?
What's so funny?

01:23.584 --> 01:24.876
I was just thinking about
all the boys

01:24.876 --> 01:26.670
you must have snuck up here
when you were a teenager.

01:26.670 --> 01:28.255
[ Chuckles ]

01:28.255 --> 01:31.425
Oh, what makes you think
they're all boys?

01:31.425 --> 01:33.635
The girls,
I didn't have to sneak.

01:33.635 --> 01:35.679
Hmm.

01:35.679 --> 01:37.681
When did your dad become cool
with you bringing boys home?

01:37.681 --> 01:38.849
[ Chuckles ]

01:38.849 --> 01:40.309
Oh, sweetie.

01:43.770 --> 01:45.814
If my father knew
you were in here,

01:45.814 --> 01:47.816
he would chop you up
and use you to fertilize

01:47.816 --> 01:48.984
next year's Chardonnay.

01:48.984 --> 01:51.987
[ Laughs ]

01:51.987 --> 01:53.822
♪♪

01:53.822 --> 01:55.824
[ Music stops ]

01:56.158 --> 01:59.161
[ Mariachi music playing ]

01:59.161 --> 02:02.164
[ Singing in Spanish ]

02:02.164 --> 02:10.422
♪♪

02:10.422 --> 02:18.722
♪♪

02:18.722 --> 02:19.765
[ Speaking Spanish ]

02:24.561 --> 02:25.687
10 minutes, please.

02:28.774 --> 02:30.484
[ Speaking Spanish ]

02:32.444 --> 02:33.320
Quesadillas?

02:36.365 --> 02:37.699
Quesadillas.

02:40.702 --> 02:42.120
<i>Buenos dias, Marta.</i>

02:42.120 --> 02:43.580
<i>Buenos dias, Señora.</i>

02:43.580 --> 02:45.040
Where is Mr. Sandoval?

02:45.040 --> 02:47.084
He went to
the vineyard early.

02:47.084 --> 02:48.794
He said he has something
to take care of.

02:48.794 --> 02:58.553
♪♪

02:58.553 --> 03:08.355
♪♪

03:08.355 --> 03:18.156
♪♪

03:19.032 --> 03:22.369
♪♪

03:35.132 --> 03:36.716
Hey, Pa!

03:36.716 --> 03:38.385
There he is.
Morning.

03:38.385 --> 03:39.553
Getting settled?

03:39.553 --> 03:41.388
Ah, between Lettie and Marta
taking care of me,

03:41.388 --> 03:42.222
I may never move out.

03:42.222 --> 03:43.390
[ Chuckles ]

03:43.390 --> 03:44.558
Well, I hope you don't.

03:44.558 --> 03:46.143
We have a lot of lost time
to make up for.

03:46.143 --> 03:47.144
Yeah.

03:47.144 --> 03:48.395
I looked over
the yield estimates ‐‐

03:48.395 --> 03:50.480
we're in line to have
our biggest harvest yet.

03:50.480 --> 03:52.941
Heritage House has never been
in a stronger position.

03:56.778 --> 03:59.823
I don't see anything in
the reports to be worried about.

03:59.823 --> 04:01.408
The threats
you don't see coming

04:01.408 --> 04:03.118
are the ones
that'll kill you.

04:04.453 --> 04:07.289
Mm.
One month till harvest.

04:07.289 --> 04:09.833
Just make sure we have the vats
to accommodate.

04:09.833 --> 04:11.751
I'll let Veronica know.

04:12.752 --> 04:14.296
I haven't seen her this morning.
Have you?

04:16.131 --> 04:18.592
It's not like her
to be late.

04:18.592 --> 04:21.845
♪♪

04:21.845 --> 04:25.640
[ Hospital intercom chatter ]

04:25.640 --> 04:26.767
<i>Hola.</i>

04:26.767 --> 04:28.477
I'm Veronica Sandoval.

04:28.477 --> 04:30.937
Cruz is one of
our employees.

04:30.937 --> 04:32.230
[ Monitors beeping ]

04:32.230 --> 04:35.233
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

04:35.233 --> 04:36.359
♪♪

04:36.359 --> 04:37.819
Ms. Sandoval.

04:37.819 --> 04:39.321
Sheriff.

04:39.321 --> 04:41.156
Hi.
How is he?

04:41.156 --> 04:42.491
Still unconscious.

04:42.491 --> 04:43.909
It's been touch and go.

04:43.909 --> 04:45.035
W‐What about the car?

04:45.035 --> 04:46.328
♪♪

04:46.328 --> 04:49.998
Well, we haven't been able to
find it yet.

04:49.998 --> 04:52.959
But don't worry,
we're zeroing in on that driver.

04:52.959 --> 04:56.463
And if Cruz Delgado dies,
the charge will be murder.

04:56.463 --> 05:05.680
♪♪

05:05.680 --> 05:08.767
When was the last time
you saw him work like that?

05:08.767 --> 05:10.060
You see, Lettie?

05:10.060 --> 05:12.312
I know I embarrassed him
the other night at that party,

05:12.312 --> 05:14.356
but tough love.
That's what that boy needed.

05:17.442 --> 05:18.401
Good morning, Carmen!

05:18.401 --> 05:19.444
No, no, no!

05:19.444 --> 05:21.154
Why don't you come in
and say hi?

05:21.154 --> 05:22.280
Good morning.

05:22.280 --> 05:23.532
How are you, <i>cariño?</i>

05:23.532 --> 05:24.533
How'd you sleep?

05:24.533 --> 05:25.992
Great.
Like a baby.

05:25.992 --> 05:27.869
I'm making Café de Olla
if you want some.

05:27.869 --> 05:29.412
Yeah.
<i>Gracias, Papi.</i>

05:29.412 --> 05:30.956
Maybe later?
Not now?

05:30.956 --> 05:32.666
No.

05:32.666 --> 05:35.168
♪♪

05:37.504 --> 05:38.588
<i>No hablo.</i>

05:38.588 --> 05:39.840
Sorry.

05:42.551 --> 05:44.553
I should probably,
uh, go to school.

05:44.553 --> 05:45.887
Have a great day, son.

05:45.887 --> 05:47.472
<i>Adios, bebe.</i>

05:47.472 --> 05:49.182
Bye.

05:49.182 --> 05:51.518
♪♪

05:51.518 --> 05:54.020
Lettie, did you ever keep
anything,

05:54.020 --> 05:57.232
photos or anything,
from before?

05:58.400 --> 06:00.360
No.
'Cause I'd understand
if you did.

06:00.360 --> 06:01.862
Even I kept a few things.

06:01.862 --> 06:03.905
♪♪

06:03.905 --> 06:06.116
No, no.
I‐I got rid of everything.

06:06.116 --> 06:08.451
♪♪

06:08.451 --> 06:11.204
Joe, what Mateo said
the other night ‐‐

06:11.204 --> 06:13.665
you know he would never
use that against us.

06:13.665 --> 06:14.666
You sure about that?

06:14.666 --> 06:15.959
Yeah.

06:18.879 --> 06:20.755
Mateo: It's not about releasing
20 good labels.

06:20.755 --> 06:23.925
It's about releasing one label
that's truly, truly great.

06:23.925 --> 06:25.635
And I'm ready to make
you an offer, Bob.

06:25.635 --> 06:27.470
Now, I know you've got
this auction scheduled

06:27.470 --> 06:28.847
for later today,
but if you just hold off ‐‐

06:28.847 --> 06:32.601
Look, Mateo,
I‐I'd love to sell to you.

06:32.601 --> 06:35.478
Eh, you're a throwback,
but... [ Sighs ]

06:35.478 --> 06:37.230
I gotta do
what's in my best interests.

06:37.230 --> 06:38.607
Bob, just hear me out.

06:38.607 --> 06:41.985
I'm sorry, but I do have
other interested parties.

06:41.985 --> 06:43.737
As a matter of fact,
here comes one now.

06:43.737 --> 06:45.155
[ Car door opens ]

06:47.616 --> 06:48.450
Mateo: Joe.

06:48.450 --> 06:49.409
Mateo.

06:49.409 --> 06:50.702
You're unbelievable.

06:50.702 --> 06:53.246
How you doin', Bob?
Yo.

06:53.246 --> 06:54.873
You have more acreage
than any grower in the Valley.

06:54.873 --> 06:55.790
You don't need
this land.

06:55.790 --> 06:57.125
You're just doing this
to, what?

06:57.125 --> 06:58.668
To screw me?
Ah, that's not true.

06:58.668 --> 07:00.211
I border this tract
to the south.

07:00.211 --> 07:01.963
If I let you buy it
and you fail...

07:01.963 --> 07:03.048
Oh, I won't fail.

07:03.048 --> 07:04.341
...some other grower
could scoop it up,

07:04.341 --> 07:08.219
and now I've got a competitor
next to me.

07:08.219 --> 07:10.764
You want to be
in this business?

07:10.764 --> 07:12.432
Welcome to the NFL.

07:12.432 --> 07:14.851
Outbid me if you want
this place so bad.

07:14.851 --> 07:18.647
Or...come back home.

07:18.647 --> 07:20.857
I'll give you a dozen rows
to cultivate.

07:20.857 --> 07:22.651
You can have
your own vintage.

07:22.651 --> 07:25.278
That's a hell of a lot better
than going into hock

07:25.278 --> 07:28.281
up to your eyeballs
to buy this place.

07:28.281 --> 07:30.158
What do you say, Mateo?

07:31.660 --> 07:33.995
Make your mother happy.

07:35.580 --> 07:37.290
You're scared.
[ Scoffs ] Of what?

07:37.290 --> 07:38.708
Competing against you?

07:38.708 --> 07:39.793
No.

07:39.793 --> 07:42.045
Of what I know.

07:42.045 --> 07:43.880
Isn't that right,
"Carlos?"

07:43.880 --> 07:47.467
♪♪

07:47.467 --> 07:49.260
It's always
a pleasure, Joe.

07:49.260 --> 07:58.395
♪♪

07:58.395 --> 08:07.529
♪♪

08:07.529 --> 08:16.705
♪♪

08:16.705 --> 08:18.873
Lettie:
[ Speaking Spanish ]

08:18.873 --> 08:20.667
"The sky blue".

08:20.667 --> 08:21.543
No, no, no.

08:21.543 --> 08:23.878
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

08:28.299 --> 08:29.509
[ Speaking Spanish ]

08:46.443 --> 08:47.861
[ Speaking Spanish ]

08:49.988 --> 08:51.698
Margaret.
I need to run to Bixby's

08:51.698 --> 08:53.074
before I head out of town.

08:53.074 --> 08:54.909
Can you, uh ‐‐ Can you get
everybody back to work here?

08:54.909 --> 08:56.745
Margaret: Yeah.

08:56.745 --> 08:57.746
Hola.

08:57.746 --> 08:59.706
[ Speaking Spanish ]

09:02.250 --> 09:03.334
<i>Vamos.</i>

09:04.586 --> 09:06.171
Hello, Miss Honeycroft!

09:06.171 --> 09:07.213
<i>Ay, wey.</i>

09:07.213 --> 09:10.925
Uh, nice day.

09:10.925 --> 09:13.303
I'm Billy.

09:13.303 --> 09:15.930
Uh, this is
my brother, Joe.

09:15.930 --> 09:17.557
Lunch break's over, guys.

09:17.557 --> 09:19.392
Lot 16 needs leafing.

09:21.728 --> 09:26.149
[ Speaking Spanish ]

09:26.149 --> 09:28.276
"To ask".
"To axe".

09:28.276 --> 09:30.361
[ Speaking Spanish ]

09:30.361 --> 09:31.488
Ask.

09:31.488 --> 09:34.657
Oh, to ask.

09:34.657 --> 09:37.702
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

09:43.041 --> 09:44.584
You're a good teacher.

09:45.794 --> 09:46.878
Eh, thank you.

09:46.878 --> 09:48.379
Mm‐hmm.

09:52.217 --> 09:53.676
I'm Margaret.

09:53.676 --> 09:54.928
What's your name?

09:54.928 --> 09:57.263
Uh, it's Lettie.

09:58.640 --> 10:00.391
That's a pretty name.

10:00.391 --> 10:01.434
Where are you from?

10:01.434 --> 10:03.770
I'm...uh...

10:03.770 --> 10:06.147
Jalisco.
It's in Mexico.

10:06.147 --> 10:08.316
All three of us. We're on
the guest worker program.

10:08.316 --> 10:09.317
Yeah.
Oh.

10:09.317 --> 10:11.152
Awesome.

10:11.152 --> 10:13.363
My dad barely speaks Spanish,
but one day,

10:13.363 --> 10:15.156
I'll be running
this place.

10:15.156 --> 10:17.992
I want to be able to speak
to the workers.

10:17.992 --> 10:19.494
Can you teach me?

10:20.995 --> 10:23.665
<i>Ay, pues</i> ‐‐ I‐I don't know,
Miss Honeycroft ‐‐

10:23.665 --> 10:24.999
Margaret.

10:24.999 --> 10:27.585
I‐I'll pay you, obviously.

10:27.585 --> 10:30.004
How does $5 an hour sound?

10:32.465 --> 10:34.384
Yeah, I‐I'll do it.
Hm.

10:34.384 --> 10:36.052
But for $10.

10:36.052 --> 10:38.304
♪♪

10:38.304 --> 10:40.140
$10 it is.

10:40.140 --> 10:43.143
♪♪

10:43.143 --> 10:44.769
Thank you.

10:44.769 --> 10:47.188
♪♪

10:47.188 --> 10:49.232
[ Speaking Spanish ]

10:49.232 --> 10:52.277
[ Speaking Spanish ]

10:52.277 --> 10:55.280
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

10:55.280 --> 10:58.158
♪♪

10:58.158 --> 10:59.576
Antonio.

10:59.576 --> 11:01.035
Would you like
something to eat?

11:01.035 --> 11:02.370
No thanks, Margaret.

11:02.370 --> 11:03.621
I'm full.
Lettie made breakfast.

11:03.621 --> 11:05.498
[ Chuckles ]

11:05.498 --> 11:07.041
What's the latest?

11:07.041 --> 11:08.626
I think there's something wrong
with Veronica.

11:08.626 --> 11:11.337
She missed a meeting, and she
never misses a meeting.

11:11.337 --> 11:12.380
Something at work?

11:12.380 --> 11:14.382
Homefront, maybe.

11:14.382 --> 11:16.342
Like what?

11:16.342 --> 11:19.137
Well, you should call her
and find out.

11:19.137 --> 11:21.848
She hasn't responded to any of
my attempts to reach out.

11:21.848 --> 11:23.766
Not once
since the day I left.

11:23.766 --> 11:25.643
Since Joe forced you out.

11:25.643 --> 11:27.145
Don't forget that.

11:27.145 --> 11:29.063
[ Sighs ]

11:29.063 --> 11:30.899
Well, keep your eyes open.

11:30.899 --> 11:32.984
If you sense
any vulnerabilities,

11:32.984 --> 11:35.737
any points of weakness...

11:35.737 --> 11:37.947
There is one thing.

11:37.947 --> 11:40.408
Could be nothing,
but, uh,

11:40.408 --> 11:42.493
the other night
at the anniversary party,

11:42.493 --> 11:44.579
Mateo said a name ‐‐

11:44.579 --> 11:46.164
Carlos Rincón.

11:46.164 --> 11:48.791
Do you have any idea
who that is?

11:48.791 --> 11:50.084
No.

11:50.084 --> 11:51.586
Oh.

11:51.586 --> 11:53.379
Well, whoever he is,
just hearing his name

11:53.379 --> 11:54.547
gave Joe a start.

11:54.547 --> 11:56.341
He tried to hide it,
but I don't think

11:56.341 --> 11:58.718
I've ever seen my pa
so rattled.

11:58.718 --> 12:00.053
♪♪

12:00.053 --> 12:02.889
Then let's find out
who Carlos Rincón is.

12:02.889 --> 12:03.890
♪♪

12:07.310 --> 12:09.687
♪♪

12:09.687 --> 12:11.606
[ Singing in Spanish ]

12:11.606 --> 12:12.899
Sorry about this morning.

12:12.899 --> 12:14.484
I had some car trouble.
It's okay.

12:14.484 --> 12:15.485
I had to catch an Uber.

12:15.485 --> 12:16.736
Antonio covered for you.

12:16.736 --> 12:19.822
Listen, I got a call
from the sheriff.

12:19.822 --> 12:21.616
She said you went by
the hospital.

12:21.616 --> 12:23.201
Mm‐hmm.
Veronica,
I thought I told you

12:23.201 --> 12:25.453
to keep your distance
from Cruz Delgado.

12:25.453 --> 12:26.788
He works for us, Pa.

12:26.788 --> 12:28.498
It sends a message
to the rest of our employees

12:28.498 --> 12:29.582
that we actually care.

12:29.582 --> 12:31.668
Joe: No, no, no, no.
He does not work for us.

12:31.668 --> 12:33.544
This guy was dealing
phony work papers.

12:33.544 --> 12:34.963
He's trouble, okay?

12:34.963 --> 12:36.422
I want you to stay away
from him.

12:36.422 --> 12:37.674
Yeah, well,
with all due respect,

12:37.674 --> 12:40.009
I can decide that
for myself.

12:40.134 --> 12:42.136
I'm gonna go
to the office.

12:43.721 --> 12:45.974
The hell got into her?

12:51.020 --> 12:53.398
I didn't think
I'd see you again.

12:54.649 --> 12:56.818
Not after the way I acted
the other day.

12:56.818 --> 12:59.237
I don't go to church
much anymore.

12:59.237 --> 13:03.866
Every day Rosa was gone,
I lit a candle to St. Jude.

13:03.866 --> 13:06.911
Guess old habits die hard,
eh, Billy?

13:08.496 --> 13:09.664
How's our son?

13:09.664 --> 13:11.332
<i>Our</i> son?

13:13.459 --> 13:16.337
Now you care,
after all these years?

13:16.337 --> 13:19.424
I never wanted to
leave you.

13:19.424 --> 13:21.384
But it was the best thing
for Mateo.

13:21.384 --> 13:22.969
For both of you.

13:22.969 --> 13:25.305
I had to heal.

13:25.305 --> 13:26.347
It's been a long road.

13:26.347 --> 13:27.974
Yeah, apparently.

13:27.974 --> 13:30.226
Lettie, you think I wanted to
come back here?

13:30.226 --> 13:33.938
All the pain
this place has caused me?

13:33.938 --> 13:35.732
I don't know why the Bishop
sent me here,

13:35.732 --> 13:39.444
but there must be
a reason.

13:39.444 --> 13:41.195
God is never wrong.

13:44.741 --> 13:45.908
[ Door closes ]

13:45.908 --> 13:49.078
He is wrong this time.

13:49.078 --> 13:51.748
♪♪

13:51.748 --> 13:53.249
Father Collins:
Mrs. Sandoval.
Hi.

13:53.249 --> 13:54.876
Is Junior feeling
any better?

13:56.294 --> 13:58.588
Mm.
You did call him in
sick today?

13:58.588 --> 13:59.672
Yes, of course.

13:59.672 --> 14:01.007
Because a couple of his friends
are also out.

14:01.007 --> 14:02.800
I'd hate to think
they skipped school.

14:02.800 --> 14:05.011
No, no.
He's home with fever.

14:05.011 --> 14:06.137
Oh.

14:06.137 --> 14:06.929
Give him my best.

14:06.929 --> 14:08.765
Thank you.
Thanks.

14:08.765 --> 14:11.642
♪♪

14:11.642 --> 14:13.436
I can help you find him.

14:13.436 --> 14:15.480
Please, Billy.

14:15.480 --> 14:17.815
Don't make this any harder.

14:17.815 --> 14:19.484
♪♪

14:23.404 --> 14:26.491
[ Doorbell rings ]

14:38.252 --> 14:39.087
Okay.

14:48.054 --> 14:49.138
Oh.

14:49.138 --> 14:51.724
Marta, say hello
to Lettie.

14:51.724 --> 14:53.893
<i>Hola,</i> Marta.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.812
<i>Encantada.</i>

14:58.397 --> 15:00.274
Thank you.

15:00.942 --> 15:02.985
What's next?

15:02.985 --> 15:04.779
Um, "hermano".

15:04.779 --> 15:06.614
It means brother.

15:06.614 --> 15:07.990
<i>"Hermano".</i>

15:07.990 --> 15:09.242
Yeah.
<i>Muy bien.</i>

15:09.242 --> 15:10.868
I have an <i>"hermano".</i>

15:10.868 --> 15:12.411
<i>Sí.</i>

15:12.411 --> 15:14.455
He's in France now,
studying viticulture.

15:14.455 --> 15:16.958
Oh, wow.
He's gonna be a wine maker
some day.

15:16.958 --> 15:18.376
Okay.

15:18.376 --> 15:21.045
My father doesn't think women
are cut out to be wine makers,

15:21.045 --> 15:23.005
but I'm going to prove him
wrong.

15:25.424 --> 15:27.009
You are.

15:27.009 --> 15:28.761
♪♪

15:28.761 --> 15:31.097
What's next?

15:31.097 --> 15:32.974
<i>"Hermana".</i>

15:32.974 --> 15:36.269
Sister.

15:36.269 --> 15:38.771
You have a sister.

15:38.771 --> 15:40.648
Uh‐huh.
What's her name?

15:40.648 --> 15:42.650
Eh, Rosa.
Thank you.

15:42.650 --> 15:43.985
Yeah.

15:43.985 --> 15:46.571
Um...[ Chuckles ]
yeah, she ‐‐

15:46.571 --> 15:49.073
she's still in Mexico.

15:49.073 --> 15:51.617
But one day,
we will see each other again.

15:52.952 --> 15:55.496
I can tell
you two are close.

15:55.496 --> 16:01.043
♪♪

16:01.043 --> 16:04.297
It's beautiful up here.

16:04.297 --> 16:06.424
Yes.

16:06.424 --> 16:08.217
It is.

16:08.217 --> 16:14.515
♪♪

16:14.515 --> 16:20.813
♪♪

16:20.813 --> 16:23.858
[ Button clicks,
garage door opens ]

16:29.697 --> 16:31.282
I thought you were headed to
the office.

16:31.282 --> 16:34.035
I was. I am.
I'm headed there now.

16:34.035 --> 16:41.584
♪♪

16:41.584 --> 16:43.211
You hit that man.

16:43.211 --> 16:44.921
Wh‐‐ What?
Who?

16:44.921 --> 16:46.839
Cruz Delgado?

16:46.839 --> 16:49.717
You think I ‐‐
C‐Come on, Carmen.

16:49.717 --> 16:53.304
♪♪

16:53.304 --> 16:55.056
[ Sighs ]

16:55.056 --> 16:56.641
♪♪

16:56.641 --> 16:58.851
I don't ‐‐ I don't know
what to do.

16:58.851 --> 16:59.936
♪♪

17:03.481 --> 17:04.941
How'd you know?
The night of Papi's party.

17:04.941 --> 17:06.859
You were really upset.

17:06.859 --> 17:08.861
Plus, the Uber,
your "car trouble".

17:08.861 --> 17:12.156
But honestly, what cinched it
was Papi telling you

17:12.156 --> 17:14.992
to do something
and you not doing it.

17:14.992 --> 17:17.119
Yeah. That's more of
a you thing, huh?

17:17.119 --> 17:19.163
Mm.

17:19.163 --> 17:20.915
I went to
the hospital, Carmen.

17:20.915 --> 17:22.583
It was bad.

17:22.583 --> 17:24.418
I don't know. I think I should
just turn myself in.

17:24.418 --> 17:27.004
No.
You should not do that.

17:27.004 --> 17:29.090
Hey.
<i>Mira me.</i>

17:29.090 --> 17:31.425
You're a good person.

17:31.425 --> 17:34.554
You're the best wife and mother
that I know.

17:34.554 --> 17:37.890
And you're a kickass CEO.

17:37.890 --> 17:41.561
What happened was horrible,
but it was a mistake.

17:41.561 --> 17:43.396
You're not throwing
your life away.

17:43.396 --> 17:45.898
You worked too damn hard.

17:47.275 --> 17:48.776
I didn't know
you felt that way.

17:48.776 --> 17:50.778
I'm gonna help you, V.

17:51.737 --> 17:53.614
Thanks so much
for helping me pack.

17:53.614 --> 17:55.324
Yeah.
It's the least I could do

17:55.324 --> 17:57.660
for letting me stay here.

17:57.660 --> 18:00.746
So, the place
that I'm renting,

18:00.746 --> 18:02.915
it's got a spare bedroom.

18:02.915 --> 18:03.958
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

18:03.958 --> 18:05.876
I‐I have stayed
for too long.

18:05.876 --> 18:07.795
Oh.
No, you haven't.

18:07.795 --> 18:10.923
Mateo, you're sleeping
on your couch.

18:10.923 --> 18:14.927
[ Chuckles ]
It's a very comfy couch.

18:14.927 --> 18:17.430
[ Vehicle approaches ]

18:19.640 --> 18:20.975
[ Car door opens ]

18:20.975 --> 18:22.935
[ Car door closes ]

18:22.935 --> 18:24.562
Hi, Daniela.

18:24.562 --> 18:26.439
I didn't expect
to see you here.

18:26.439 --> 18:29.442
Oh.
Mwah.

18:29.442 --> 18:30.735
I'm not talking to him.

18:30.735 --> 18:32.570
He wants to
make things right.

18:32.570 --> 18:35.656
Mateo, please.

18:35.656 --> 18:37.783
Just talk to him.

18:37.783 --> 18:39.577
For me.

18:43.039 --> 18:45.041
[ Speaking Spanish ]

18:46.667 --> 18:48.294
So, you're good,
I hope?

18:48.294 --> 18:49.754
Yes.
Yeah?

18:49.754 --> 18:51.088
Where have you
been staying?

18:52.590 --> 18:54.133
[ Car door closes ]

18:55.384 --> 18:57.386
If you're set on starting
your own label,

18:57.386 --> 18:58.554
I can't stop you,

18:58.554 --> 19:01.307
but that Haskins tract
is too big for you.

19:01.307 --> 19:02.558
That's your opinion.

19:02.558 --> 19:05.311
The money that property
will go for at auction?

19:05.311 --> 19:08.230
For you, that's all your savings
and a mountain of debt.

19:08.230 --> 19:11.817
For me,
it's a rounding error.

19:11.817 --> 19:14.820
Yeah, I just don't think I'm
gonna have to worry about that.

19:14.820 --> 19:16.447
See, I don't think
you're gonna be at that auction.

19:16.447 --> 19:17.448
Why is that?

19:17.448 --> 19:19.742
Well, if I ever let it slip

19:19.742 --> 19:23.204
that Joe Sandoval
is a fiction, a fraud,

19:23.204 --> 19:24.705
tell me, what will
your shareholders think?

19:24.705 --> 19:26.082
You think it would affect
your stock price?

19:26.082 --> 19:27.041
Your reputation?

19:27.041 --> 19:28.000
You think ICE
would like to know,

19:28.000 --> 19:30.336
maybe make an example
out of you?

19:30.336 --> 19:32.171
You won't be at that auction
because you're too smart

19:32.171 --> 19:34.173
to lose everything
you've built.

19:34.173 --> 19:37.343
You can play that card,
hurt me,

19:37.343 --> 19:41.514
maybe even bring me down.

19:41.514 --> 19:43.307
Just remember,

19:43.307 --> 19:46.686
I'm not the only one
who's undocumented.

19:46.686 --> 19:49.355
And it's just not Daniela.

19:49.355 --> 19:52.692
Are you willing to blow up
your mother's life, too?

19:52.692 --> 19:56.737
♪♪

19:56.737 --> 19:58.739
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

20:11.377 --> 20:12.378
No, no.

20:23.264 --> 20:26.225
[ Speaking Spanish ]

20:31.689 --> 20:32.940
[ Speaking Spanish ]

20:32.940 --> 20:34.859
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

20:34.859 --> 20:37.194
[ Speaking Spanish ]

20:37.194 --> 20:45.453
♪♪

20:45.453 --> 20:53.711
♪♪

20:53.711 --> 21:01.969
♪♪

21:01.969 --> 21:10.269
♪♪

21:10.269 --> 21:18.569
♪♪

21:18.569 --> 21:20.988
Oh.

21:20.988 --> 21:21.989
♪♪

21:21.989 --> 21:24.867
Ma.

21:24.867 --> 21:27.620
Hungry.

21:27.620 --> 21:29.038
What's for lunch?

21:30.080 --> 21:31.499
What's for lunch?

21:31.499 --> 21:33.584
♪♪

21:33.584 --> 21:36.712
I've seen this before,
with Mateo's father.

21:36.712 --> 21:39.131
I've seen what can happen
to a good man.

21:39.131 --> 21:42.218
Well, I heard Uncle Billy
wasn't so great.

21:42.218 --> 21:43.552
At the end? No.

21:43.552 --> 21:45.638
But when I first met him,
he was the kindest,

21:45.638 --> 21:49.225
most generous man
I ever met.

21:49.225 --> 21:51.644
Then he threw it all away.

21:51.644 --> 21:54.897
Liquor and drugs.

21:54.897 --> 21:57.399
If I tell your father
what I found in your room,

21:57.399 --> 22:00.528
he'll kill you, Junior.

22:00.528 --> 22:02.154
Or send you off
to a military school,

22:02.154 --> 22:03.614
and that'll be
the end of that.

22:03.614 --> 22:05.199
No, he won't.

22:05.199 --> 22:08.369
Joe! Can you come here
for a moment?
Whoa, Ma, Ma, Ma, Ma.

22:08.369 --> 22:10.371
Junior, wants to
show you something!
Ma, stop!

22:10.371 --> 22:12.456
He's in the den!

22:12.456 --> 22:14.208
Do I have
your attention now?

22:15.376 --> 22:19.171
Do I have
your attention now?

22:19.171 --> 22:20.005
Yes.

22:20.005 --> 22:21.465
Repeat that.

22:21.465 --> 22:22.842
Yes, ma'am.

22:22.842 --> 22:25.302
Marta, get rid of this.

22:30.516 --> 22:31.809
I'm proud of you, Mateo.

22:31.809 --> 22:33.644
It's a big move.

22:33.644 --> 22:36.397
It's not easy,
standing up to Joe.

22:37.398 --> 22:41.026
Yeah, that was rough.

22:41.026 --> 22:42.403
You know, to be honest,
I thought Joe sent you here

22:42.403 --> 22:44.405
to talk me out of
going to that auction.

22:44.405 --> 22:46.615
[ Scoffs ] Not at all.

22:46.615 --> 22:48.909
If you can outbid him,
do it.

22:48.909 --> 22:51.036
We both know that he doesn't
need the land.

22:51.036 --> 22:58.794
♪♪

22:58.794 --> 23:00.504
Yeah, I've been meaning to
ask you, though,

23:00.504 --> 23:02.214
about that night
at the anniversary party.

23:02.214 --> 23:05.718
What was that about?
[ Laughs ]

23:05.718 --> 23:07.386
Who's Carlos Rincón?

23:08.304 --> 23:10.264
Who's...

23:10.264 --> 23:12.057
Is that someone I should be
worried about, or...

23:12.057 --> 23:15.185
Um...

23:15.185 --> 23:16.478
Yeah, I was pretty wasted
that night.

23:16.478 --> 23:17.771
I don't remember.

23:17.771 --> 23:19.940
[ Chuckles ]

23:19.940 --> 23:21.775
♪♪

23:21.775 --> 23:23.944
[ Doorbell rings ]

23:23.944 --> 23:25.195
Hola, Marta.

23:25.195 --> 23:26.447
<i>Buenas.</i>
[ Speaking Spanish ]

23:47.259 --> 23:49.303
He's in Santa Ynez
on business.

23:49.303 --> 23:51.263
He'll be back tomorrow.

23:51.263 --> 23:53.432
I'll get Miss Honeycroft.

23:56.435 --> 23:58.729
Billy.

24:08.405 --> 24:11.200
[ Speaking Spanish ]

24:11.200 --> 24:12.201
Hi, guys.

24:12.201 --> 24:13.994
Hey.
I'm glad
you could make it.

24:13.994 --> 24:15.245
I was just about to get in
the pool,

24:15.245 --> 24:17.164
if you want to change
into your suits.

24:17.164 --> 24:19.291
♪♪

24:19.291 --> 24:20.918
Um...

24:20.918 --> 24:22.795
♪♪

24:22.795 --> 24:25.255
I don't think my dad's trunks
will fit you.

24:25.255 --> 24:27.049
Maybe you could cut off
your jeans.

24:27.049 --> 24:28.509
[ Giggles ]

24:28.968 --> 24:29.927
[ Speaking Spanish ]

24:34.098 --> 24:35.140
Gracias.

24:35.140 --> 24:38.143
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

24:38.143 --> 24:45.651
♪♪

24:45.651 --> 24:53.117
♪♪

24:53.117 --> 25:00.541
♪♪

25:00.541 --> 25:02.251
We're the same size.

25:02.251 --> 25:07.256
♪♪

25:07.256 --> 25:08.799
Like <i>hermanas.</i>

25:08.799 --> 25:17.558
♪♪

25:17.558 --> 25:18.809
Good afternoon,
ladies and gentlemen.

25:18.809 --> 25:20.519
The subject is
the Haskins tract.

25:20.519 --> 25:23.605
21 acres of vine rows and all
assets appurtenant thereto,

25:23.605 --> 25:26.108
including the winery and all
the juice in the barrels.

25:26.108 --> 25:27.735
Bidding will open
at $2 million.

25:27.735 --> 25:29.236
Can I get $2 million?

25:29.236 --> 25:31.238
$2 million.
Can I get 2.1?

25:31.238 --> 25:32.781
2.1.
Can I get 2.2?

25:32.781 --> 25:34.074
2.2.
2.3?

25:34.074 --> 25:35.284
Can I get ‐‐ 2.3.
Thank you, sir.

25:35.284 --> 25:37.077
Can I get 2.4?
2.4.

25:37.077 --> 25:37.953
Gentleman is determined.

25:37.953 --> 25:40.080
Can I get ‐‐
$3 million.

25:40.080 --> 25:41.749
Bid is $3 million.

25:41.749 --> 25:43.083
Can I get 3.1?

25:43.083 --> 25:43.917
3.1.

25:43.917 --> 25:45.627
3.1.
3.1 is the bid.

25:45.627 --> 25:48.338
Can I get ‐‐
$4 million.

25:48.338 --> 25:50.841
The bid is $4 million
to Mr. Joe Sandoval.

25:50.841 --> 25:52.634
Can I get 4.1?

25:52.634 --> 25:54.928
Are there any bidders
at 4.1?

25:54.928 --> 25:58.140
The high bid is $4 million
to Mr. Joe Sandoval.

25:58.140 --> 26:00.392
Going once,
going twice...

26:00.392 --> 26:01.727
Margaret:
$5 million!

26:01.727 --> 26:03.020
[ Crowd gasps ]

26:03.020 --> 26:09.943
♪♪

26:13.739 --> 26:14.948
5 and a half.

26:14.948 --> 26:16.325
Auctioneer:
5‐and‐a‐half million.

26:16.325 --> 26:17.451
5‐and‐a‐half million
is the bid.

26:17.451 --> 26:18.535
6!
6 million!

26:18.535 --> 26:20.662
6‐and‐a‐half!
7!

26:20.662 --> 26:23.624
8.
$8 million.

26:23.624 --> 26:26.835
$8 million is the bid.

26:26.835 --> 26:30.547
Going once,
going twice...

26:30.547 --> 26:33.300
sold for $8 million
to Mr. Joe Sandoval.

26:33.300 --> 26:36.804
♪♪

26:36.804 --> 26:39.640
Congratulations, Joe.

26:39.640 --> 26:42.267
Buying this place wouldn't have
gotten you any closer

26:42.267 --> 26:44.686
to taking over
Heritage House.

26:44.686 --> 26:46.647
I know. I just wanted to
see you pay

26:46.647 --> 26:48.232
three times
what this dump is worth.

26:48.232 --> 26:50.150
[ Chuckles ]
Do you wake up in the morning

26:50.150 --> 26:51.944
thinking of ways
to screw me over?

26:51.944 --> 26:54.655
[ Gasps ]
Oh, Joe.

26:55.906 --> 26:58.826
I go to bed
thinking about it, too.

27:00.410 --> 27:03.038
Say hi to Lettie for me.

27:07.292 --> 27:09.336
Congratulations.

27:10.879 --> 27:12.297
And thank you.

27:12.297 --> 27:14.091
This just drives me
that much harder.

27:31.692 --> 27:33.402
[ Chuckles ]
Hey, guys.

27:33.402 --> 27:36.071
♪♪

27:36.071 --> 27:37.364
Hello.

27:37.364 --> 27:43.287
♪♪

27:43.287 --> 27:46.039
♪ The boy with a thorn
in his side ♪

27:48.041 --> 27:49.960
♪♪

27:49.960 --> 27:53.005
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

27:55.382 --> 27:58.427
[ Laughter ]

27:59.094 --> 28:01.305
Aren't you gonna get in?

28:01.305 --> 28:02.347
No, you know?

28:08.437 --> 28:10.647
That's not a good idea.
Joe can't swim.

28:10.647 --> 28:13.525
You've never had
a swim lesson?

28:17.946 --> 28:20.198
Ay, Joe.
I guess, huh.

28:20.198 --> 28:21.366
What'd he say?

28:21.366 --> 28:23.035
[ Speaking Spanish ]

28:23.035 --> 28:24.703
I heard "rich girl".

28:24.703 --> 28:28.081
You ‐‐ You act like friend,
<i>pero</i> you're no friend.

28:28.081 --> 28:29.917
[ Speaking Spanish ]

28:29.917 --> 28:30.876
That's not true.

28:30.876 --> 28:32.669
[ Speaking Spanish ]

28:37.049 --> 28:38.342
What's he saying?

28:42.971 --> 28:44.014
Speak English.

28:48.769 --> 28:51.355
Lunch. My ‐‐ My brother,
he gets hungry.

28:51.355 --> 28:54.274
Great. I'll get us
something to drink.

29:02.991 --> 29:06.453
[ Speaking Spanish ]

29:06.453 --> 29:08.830
[ Laughs ]

29:08.830 --> 29:09.831
How's this?

29:09.831 --> 29:11.959
[ Speaking Spanish ]

29:11.959 --> 29:13.585
[ Both laugh ]

29:13.585 --> 29:16.088
"Honeycroft Chardonno".

29:16.088 --> 29:17.798
Chardonnay.
Chardonnay?

29:17.798 --> 29:19.216
Yeah.

29:23.929 --> 29:27.224
But, Carmen, this is crazy.

29:27.224 --> 29:28.600
Shouldn't we be taking it
to, like,

29:28.600 --> 29:29.768
a chop shop or something?

29:29.768 --> 29:31.478
Chop shop?
Okay, Vin Diesel.

29:31.478 --> 29:33.855
Veronica, criminals take
their car to a chop shop.

29:33.855 --> 29:36.650
Sandovals take their car
to the dealer.

29:36.650 --> 29:37.943
Carmen.
Hi, Ted.

29:37.943 --> 29:39.361
Back again?
Yeah.

29:39.361 --> 29:40.821
This is my sister,
Veronica.

29:40.821 --> 29:42.155
Oh, hi.
Hi.

29:42.155 --> 29:43.615
What'd you, uh,
smack into?

29:43.615 --> 29:45.283
Oh.
Actually, it wasn't her.

29:45.283 --> 29:46.618
It was me.
She was nice enough

29:46.618 --> 29:49.454
to lend me her car,
I was texting...

29:49.454 --> 29:51.415
Carmen.
I know.

29:51.415 --> 29:53.542
It's statistically as dangerous
as drunk driving.

29:53.542 --> 29:55.711
Seriously, be careful.

29:55.711 --> 29:58.588
Should I, uh, bill it
to your dad's account?

29:58.588 --> 30:01.299
Actually, you know,
he'll go crazy

30:01.299 --> 30:03.010
if he knows I crashed
my sister's car,

30:03.010 --> 30:08.473
so I was thinking if I pay you
in cash, we'll just...

30:08.473 --> 30:10.600
No one will ever know
a thing.

30:10.600 --> 30:11.893
Ah!
You're the best.

30:11.893 --> 30:13.061
How's the little boy?

30:13.061 --> 30:13.854
[ Cellphone clicks ]

30:14.479 --> 30:17.482
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my God!

30:17.482 --> 30:19.026
<i>Que hermoso!</i>

30:19.026 --> 30:20.861
Look at him,
he looks just like you!

30:20.861 --> 30:22.612
♪♪

30:22.612 --> 30:24.573
Marta said
you were looking for me.

30:24.573 --> 30:31.747
♪♪

30:31.747 --> 30:33.915
Our son's a drug addict.

30:33.915 --> 30:35.584
♪♪

30:35.584 --> 30:39.963
He skipped school today,
came home wasted.

30:39.963 --> 30:42.007
♪♪

30:42.007 --> 30:44.926
I lied for him,
told the principal he was sick.

30:44.926 --> 30:48.513
Covered for him, because I knew
how you'd react.

30:48.513 --> 30:49.765
I'm gonna kill that boy.

30:49.765 --> 30:52.476
You aren't gonna
do anything, Joe.

30:52.476 --> 30:56.188
I let you drive away
one of my sons.

30:56.188 --> 31:00.484
I'll be damned if I let you
drive away another.

31:00.484 --> 31:07.699
♪♪

31:07.699 --> 31:08.867
[ Door slams ]

31:08.867 --> 31:17.084
♪♪

31:17.084 --> 31:18.210
[ Chuckles ]

31:18.210 --> 31:19.711
Margaret: You guys
are such lightweights.

31:19.711 --> 31:20.879
Hey, Lettie.
Hmm?

31:20.879 --> 31:22.506
<i>Cómo se dice</i>
"lightweight"?

31:22.506 --> 31:25.842
[ Speaking Spanish ]

31:25.842 --> 31:27.928
[ Speaking Spanish ]

31:27.928 --> 31:30.013
No, no, no.
Not true.

31:30.013 --> 31:31.556
[ Chuckles ]
It's true.

31:31.556 --> 31:34.726
You grow up in a vineyard,
you learn how to drink.

31:34.726 --> 31:36.061
♪♪

31:36.061 --> 31:36.895
Who needs a refill?

31:36.895 --> 31:37.729
Mm. Yo!

31:37.729 --> 31:39.773
Ay, yo‐Joe!

31:39.773 --> 31:41.399
Yo‐Joe!

31:41.399 --> 31:42.859
[ Laughter ]

31:42.859 --> 31:44.236
Thank you.

31:47.489 --> 31:48.323
Gracias.

31:48.323 --> 31:51.743
[ Speaking Spanish ]

31:51.743 --> 31:53.495
[ Speaking Spanish ]

31:54.788 --> 31:57.082
Wait.
Wait, I know this.

31:57.082 --> 31:59.584
P'arriba,
p'abajo.

31:59.584 --> 32:01.211
P'al centro.

32:01.211 --> 32:02.838
P'adentro!

32:02.838 --> 32:04.297
[ Laughter ]

32:04.297 --> 32:06.091
She's a good student,
no?

32:06.091 --> 32:07.467
I have a good teacher.

32:07.467 --> 32:08.426
[ Laughter ]

32:08.426 --> 32:09.845
Thank you.

32:09.845 --> 32:11.179
You guys taste the fruit?

32:11.179 --> 32:12.514
Fruit?

32:12.514 --> 32:15.225
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

32:15.225 --> 32:16.935
No, I don't taste anything.

32:16.935 --> 32:19.855
<i>Mandarina.</i>

32:21.439 --> 32:22.941
<i>Cómo se dice "mandarina"?</i>

32:22.941 --> 32:24.901
Tangerine.

32:24.901 --> 32:26.153
Nice.

32:26.153 --> 32:28.530
You have a good palate.

32:28.530 --> 32:30.157
Thank you.

32:30.157 --> 32:32.367
♪♪

32:32.367 --> 32:34.077
What's "palate?"

32:34.077 --> 32:35.829
[ Laughter ]

32:35.829 --> 32:38.707
Oh, my gosh.

32:38.707 --> 32:40.250
Come on.

32:40.250 --> 32:43.086
[ Laughter ]

32:46.506 --> 32:48.925
Margaret,
can I have some water?

32:48.925 --> 32:51.469
You know where it is,
don't you?

32:51.469 --> 32:53.096
The kitchen, no?
Yeah.

32:53.096 --> 32:56.516
♪♪

32:58.768 --> 33:01.313
[ Door opens ]

33:01.313 --> 33:02.689
♪♪

33:02.689 --> 33:04.024
Honeycroft:
Margaret!

33:04.024 --> 33:06.484
Margaret, I'm home!

33:06.484 --> 33:08.403
♪♪

33:08.403 --> 33:09.696
Margaret?

33:09.696 --> 33:12.782
♪♪

33:16.953 --> 33:18.496
Margaret?

33:20.582 --> 33:22.876
[ Keys jingle ]

33:22.876 --> 33:25.378
[ Laughter in distance ]

33:28.506 --> 33:30.217
Margaret?

33:32.677 --> 33:33.887
[ Door opens ]

33:34.638 --> 33:35.972
Oh, there you are.

33:35.972 --> 33:37.015
Hi, Daddy.

33:37.015 --> 33:37.891
You're home early.

33:37.891 --> 33:40.060
Oh.
The meeting was garbage.

33:40.060 --> 33:42.854
Some fool from L. A.
saying "wine coolers"

33:42.854 --> 33:44.898
are the future
of the industry.

33:44.898 --> 33:45.899
What's a wine cooler?

33:45.899 --> 33:46.816
[ Scoffs ]
Yeah, exactly.

33:46.816 --> 33:49.027
[ Chuckles ]

33:49.402 --> 33:50.820
So, who were you
talking to?

33:50.820 --> 33:51.905
Talking to?

33:51.905 --> 33:54.115
You were talking to someone.
Who was it?

33:54.115 --> 33:55.867
Nobody.

33:55.867 --> 33:58.453
Me, Mr. Honeycroft.

33:58.453 --> 34:00.080
Oh, just you, Marta?

34:00.080 --> 34:01.790
Mm‐hmm.

34:01.790 --> 34:03.250
Alright, who's here, huh?

34:03.250 --> 34:04.376
Nobody.

34:04.376 --> 34:06.711
You sneak some boys in here
from your school?

34:06.711 --> 34:09.547
Daddy, that's ridiculous.

34:09.547 --> 34:11.549
Are you ready to get back to
our words?

34:11.549 --> 34:12.842
Whoa.
Who's this?

34:12.842 --> 34:14.302
D‐Daddy,
this is Lettie.

34:14.302 --> 34:16.596
She's helping me
learn Spanish.

34:16.596 --> 34:18.515
Mm‐hmm.
Lettie, this is my father.

34:18.515 --> 34:21.184
Well, nice to meet you.
And you.

34:21.184 --> 34:22.602
You look familiar.
Have we met?

34:22.602 --> 34:25.272
Uh, Lettie works
for us, Daddy.

34:25.272 --> 34:27.440
On the vineyard.

34:27.440 --> 34:29.734
Oh, no kidding.

34:29.734 --> 34:31.695
We can afford
a $20‐an‐hour tutor,

34:31.695 --> 34:34.072
and you hire a wetback?

34:34.072 --> 34:36.783
Marta, how about
some dinner?

34:37.826 --> 34:39.536
Lettie.

34:47.002 --> 34:51.381
♪♪

34:51.923 --> 34:53.925
You sure it's okay if I borrow
your car for a few days?

34:53.925 --> 34:56.094
[ Inhales sharply ]
Got nowhere to be.

35:01.308 --> 35:03.101
Thanks.

35:03.101 --> 35:04.603
[ Exhales sharply ]

35:07.480 --> 35:09.649
Hey.

35:11.818 --> 35:13.486
I underestimated you.

35:13.486 --> 35:14.988
Everyone does.

35:14.988 --> 35:16.990
And I've been thinking
a lot about your idea.

35:16.990 --> 35:18.033
Oh?

35:18.033 --> 35:19.826
About the label
for people in their 20s.

35:22.495 --> 35:24.831
I think Michael could help you
get it into shape.

35:24.831 --> 35:26.041
[ Exhales sharply ]

35:26.041 --> 35:29.878
V, no knock,
but I want you to talk to Papi

35:29.878 --> 35:32.255
or the board,
not your husband.

35:32.255 --> 35:34.341
Carmen, Papi and the board

35:34.341 --> 35:37.802
are not the service rep
from the dealership.

35:37.802 --> 35:39.971
You can't just charm them
into a new label,

35:39.971 --> 35:41.973
as charming as you are.

35:41.973 --> 35:43.808
[ Chuckles ]

35:43.808 --> 35:45.185
[ Sighs ]
Come on.

35:45.185 --> 35:47.812
I trusted you.

35:47.812 --> 35:49.439
Trust me?

35:50.857 --> 35:53.193
Okay.

35:53.193 --> 35:54.527
Okay.

35:54.527 --> 35:57.197
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

35:57.197 --> 35:58.156
[ Cellphone beeps ]

35:58.156 --> 36:00.116
Hello?

36:00.116 --> 36:01.868
♪♪

36:01.868 --> 36:03.411
Hi. Yes.

36:03.411 --> 36:05.580
Sheriff, hi.

36:05.580 --> 36:06.915
♪♪

36:06.915 --> 36:10.752
Thank you for calling
and letting me know.

36:10.752 --> 36:12.170
Yeah.

36:12.545 --> 36:14.005
[ Cellphone beeps ]
What?

36:14.005 --> 36:17.008
Cruz Delgado just regained
consciousness.

36:17.008 --> 36:19.594
Deputies are questioning him
in the morning.

36:19.594 --> 36:26.685
♪♪

36:33.400 --> 36:34.734
[ Car door closes ]

36:36.361 --> 36:37.570
You wanted to see me?

36:37.570 --> 36:38.905
I'm here.

36:38.905 --> 36:40.407
What do you want?

36:46.413 --> 36:47.831
I'm not giving you
the place.

36:47.831 --> 36:50.375
I'm renting it to you,
at a fair market rate.

36:50.375 --> 36:52.502
But it's your show.

36:52.502 --> 36:55.463
You can grow what you want,
cultivate what you want,

36:55.463 --> 36:58.007
be your own wine maker.

36:58.007 --> 36:59.968
I only have two conditions.

36:59.968 --> 37:00.885
Of course you do.

37:00.885 --> 37:01.970
As the owner of the tract,

37:01.970 --> 37:04.389
I want a cut of any juice
you sell.

37:04.389 --> 37:07.475
I'd say 10% is reasonable.

37:07.475 --> 37:11.104
And the other condition?

37:11.104 --> 37:12.856
Stay in your house.

37:12.856 --> 37:14.941
Your mother likes
having you close.

37:14.941 --> 37:18.570
♪♪

37:18.570 --> 37:20.739
I'll stay in my house...

37:20.739 --> 37:23.366
♪♪

37:23.366 --> 37:24.951
...but you'll take 5%.

37:24.951 --> 37:28.121
♪♪

37:28.121 --> 37:29.831
I thought you didn't think
I was a wine maker.

37:29.831 --> 37:31.624
I don't.

37:31.624 --> 37:33.668
♪♪

37:33.668 --> 37:36.463
But Old Man Honeycroft
said the same thing about me,

37:36.463 --> 37:40.675
and, well,
look how that turned out.

37:40.675 --> 37:44.095
♪♪

37:44.095 --> 37:46.014
[ Car door opens, closes ]

37:46.014 --> 37:48.057
[ Car starts ]

37:48.057 --> 37:49.601
♪♪

37:49.601 --> 37:51.519
Are you warm, Junior?

37:51.519 --> 37:54.022
Because it's cool in here,
and you look sweaty.

37:54.022 --> 37:55.064
I'm fine.

37:55.064 --> 37:58.026
No. You're not.

37:58.026 --> 38:01.654
Your body's craving the opioids
it's not getting.

38:01.654 --> 38:03.698
Father Collins
wanted to kick you out

38:03.698 --> 38:05.074
the first time
you screwed up.

38:05.074 --> 38:06.409
I had to
talk him out of it.

38:06.409 --> 38:07.994
So, if you mess up again,

38:07.994 --> 38:09.829
you're gonna make me
look like a fool.

38:09.829 --> 38:13.124
And I don't let anyone
make me look like a fool.

38:16.503 --> 38:18.213
Why'd you stick up for me?

38:18.213 --> 38:20.548
♪♪

38:20.548 --> 38:23.301
Maybe I'm a big believer
in second chances.

38:23.301 --> 38:30.433
♪♪

38:30.433 --> 38:33.394
[ Monitor beeping ]

38:47.367 --> 38:50.453
"I'm on Route 9
by the Highlands."

38:50.453 --> 38:53.456
[ Beeping quickens ]

38:53.456 --> 38:56.960
♪♪

38:56.960 --> 38:59.379
"A man got hit by a car."

38:59.379 --> 39:01.297
♪♪

39:01.297 --> 39:04.300
I know it was you.

39:04.300 --> 39:05.677
[ Car door closes ]

39:05.677 --> 39:14.519
♪♪

39:14.519 --> 39:23.403
♪♪

39:23.403 --> 39:32.245
♪♪

39:32.245 --> 39:41.087
♪♪

39:41.087 --> 39:49.929
♪♪

39:49.929 --> 39:58.813
♪♪

39:58.813 --> 40:07.697
♪♪

40:07.697 --> 40:16.623
♪♪

40:24.464 --> 40:26.466
[ Speaking Spanish ]

40:34.265 --> 40:35.600
<i>Tambien.</i>

40:39.270 --> 40:41.314
See you, Lettie.

40:41.314 --> 40:42.482
Ha.

40:42.482 --> 40:44.275
Thank you for pants.

40:45.777 --> 40:46.861
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

40:49.489 --> 40:51.324
[ Speaking Spanish ]

41:15.640 --> 41:18.643
[ Telephone ringing ]

41:20.353 --> 41:21.479
[ Speaking Spanish ]

41:32.865 --> 41:34.867
Hey, Margaret,
let's get this settled.

41:34.867 --> 41:35.952
I want you to take
a look here.

41:43.334 --> 41:46.504
♪♪

41:46.504 --> 41:48.172
[ Dial tone ]

41:48.172 --> 41:55.513
♪♪

41:55.513 --> 41:58.516
[ Line beeping ]

41:58.516 --> 42:05.815
♪♪

42:05.815 --> 42:06.816
[ Phone beeps ]

42:06.816 --> 42:12.405
♪♪

42:12.405 --> 42:18.077
♪♪

42:18.077 --> 42:20.747
[ Breathing heavily ]

42:20.747 --> 42:22.457
♪♪

42:26.002 --> 42:34.802
♪♪

